Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.21,0:00:04.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.89,0:00:07.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bring you marvelous illusions that \Nmake this town sparkle at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.90,0:00:12.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For the first time this year, \Nplease enjoy that little guy's miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.69,0:00:23.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kaito, class is starting!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.52,0:00:26.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! What do you care?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.54,0:00:26.50,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,A Notice to Kid the Phantom Thief!\NI possess a Big Jewel.\NBlue Wonder (The Miracle of the Ocean)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.50,0:00:28.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.96,0:00:30.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.04,0:00:32.58,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an6}Preparing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.01,0:00:35.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.95,0:00:38.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you be in school?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.43,0:00:40.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I left early.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.01,0:00:43.48,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,A Notice to Kid the Phantom Thief!\NI possess a Big Jewel.\NBlue Wonder (The Miracle of the Ocean)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.42,0:00:43.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have seen this advertisement.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.86,0:00:46.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's a trap, Young Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.94,0:00:49.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:50.57,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't escape from me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.57,0:00:52.40,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Ultra-high-definition Blu-ray Disc
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.40,0:00:54.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.28,0:00:57.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the Suzuki conglomerate's \Nsenior adviser,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.80,0:01:01.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,meaning he has unlimited funds\N to prepare for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.24,0:01:04.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, he's already \Nmade the first move.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.16,0:01:08.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to steal it, at least \Ndon't send an advance notice this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.29,0:01:10.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got it backwards, Jii-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.68,0:01:14.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy is openly picking a fight with \Nthe unrivaled Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.46,0:01:17.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I won't be satisfied unless I slap \Nhim back with an advance notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.72,0:01:19.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.37,0:01:24.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Toichi-sama, too. Once he made up his mind, \Nhe would see it through without fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.64,0:01:27.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how dangerous the circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.19,0:01:29.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.22,0:01:32.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm counting on you to \Nlay the groundwork, Jii-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.79,0:01:37.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose any further \Narguing would be pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.42,0:01:42.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Jii will look into all \Nthe details for you, Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.49,0:03:26.93,Signs - Thief Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)}Kid vs Conan: Miraculous Airwalking
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.77,0:03:26.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I put up a good front for Jii-chan,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.93,0:03:30.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't think my usual bag \Nof tricks will work this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.20,0:03:32.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me, Kaito.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.22,0:03:38.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Challenging hecklers who interfere with \Nyour magic are always a pain to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:45.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking you'll floor them right away\N is the height of foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.35,0:03:50.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic is not a battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.49,0:03:52.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something that entertains many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.75,0:03:54.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:58.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can divide challenging \Naudience members into two groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.81,0:04:03.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The first type wants to stand out \Nmore than the magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.33,0:04:06.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All you can do to deal with that \Nsort of person is silence them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.12,0:04:09.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Silence them...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.64,0:04:12.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's the type that is so curious,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.20,0:04:16.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,they can't stand not knowing the trick, \Neven if it means interfering with the magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.68,0:04:21.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For them, don't be bound \Nby theory, but intox...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.82,0:04:24.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.82,0:04:26.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}For them, don't be bound \Nby theory, but intox...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.61,0:04:29.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}For them, don't be bound \Nby theory, but intox...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.38,0:04:29.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Right at the important part!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:36.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid will be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.40,0:04:39.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's on the roof of the museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.78,0:04:43.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He can just run up the side of the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.16,0:04:45.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet Kid can do something like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.78,0:04:46.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can picture it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.27,0:04:49.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:53.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Has Kid accepted this challenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.96,0:04:56.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The risk is too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.44,0:04:59.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe he has a 50% chance of success.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.01,0:05:03.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be a dumbass! This is exactly \Nthe kind of challenge Kid lives for!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.23,0:05:05.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wonder how he's gonna steal it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.75,0:05:07.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait to find out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:12.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is dying to find out \Nhow I'm going to steal it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.87,0:05:15.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:18.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't just win against old man Jirokichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:21.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief is \Nall about entertaining the audience!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:29.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is Blue Wonder...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.09,0:05:32.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can fly in on a hang glider, \Ngrab it, and go, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.94,0:05:35.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.23,0:05:40.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Jirokichi has hired \Na crackerjack security team.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.51,0:05:43.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That includes a helicopter squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.69,0:05:45.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are 20 choppers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.31,0:05:48.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and even now, \Nthey're bringing in more people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:53.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That many choppers flying around will make \Nthe wind currents too choppy for a glider.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:53.87,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Jirokichi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:56.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll think of another \Nmeans of transport.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.19,0:05:58.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that will be difficult, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.66,0:05:59.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:03.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Information I received from a contractor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.70,0:06:07.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is that even possible?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.04,0:06:09.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.62,0:06:15.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jii-chan, what about the inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.40,0:06:20.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,100 surveillance cameras operating \Nat all times, catching everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.21,0:06:22.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There are no blind spots.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:25.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although cameras mean nothing \Nif I go in disguise!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.66,0:06:32.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A look at the security plan shows \Nthey mean to have {\i1}no one{\i0} inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.20,0:06:34.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I won't have anyone to impersonate...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.83,0:06:38.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, the helicopters \Nare equipped with cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.17,0:06:40.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and all of the footage that they capture
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.67,0:06:44.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,is sent to this truck parked here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.13,0:06:46.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Footage, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:56.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's a special museum \Nexhibition, a helicopter shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.97,0:07:01.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand how rich people think.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.30,0:07:12.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Young Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.42,0:07:15.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. If he's mixed up in it this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:19.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just have to show him some brilliant magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.41,0:07:22.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But how...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.05,0:07:24.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I found an opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.03,0:07:27.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That just leaves Blue Wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.05,0:07:28.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Miracle of the Sea...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.40,0:07:32.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Walking on water is a famous miracle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.54,0:07:33.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.64,0:07:38.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Kid the Phantom Thief \Nwill have to top that miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:40.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.25,0:07:41.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:45.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Reappearance" is one of the basics of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.56,0:07:47.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the same kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.98,0:07:49.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.39,0:07:53.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jii-chan, how long will it take you \Nto prepare the tools and set this up?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.18,0:07:55.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can have until Saturday...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:57.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.74,0:08:05.42,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a7}{\fad(0,1000)}I accept your kind invitation. \NThe event will take place this Sunday at 8:00 pm. \NPlease pardon my rudeness for performing\N a preliminary inspection the night before...\NKid the Phantom Thief\N\Np.s. Like the name Blue Wonder, \NI'm going to just walk right over...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.18,0:08:11.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Kid's advance notice, he's \Ngoing to do a preliminary inspection tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.78,0:08:14.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Will Kid actually appear as promised?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.82,0:08:20.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.89,0:08:24.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.88,0:08:26.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:29.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.68,0:08:37.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Young Master, we're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.74,0:08:41.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's time to start the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.97,0:08:48.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, Jii-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.67,0:08:50.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Again, be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.27,0:09:04.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All-righty...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.94,0:09:26.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's floating?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.16,0:09:27.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.29,0:09:29.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be fooled!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.18,0:09:34.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's just hanging by a wire from \Na black ad balloon or something!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.02,0:09:38.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nab him and get back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.60,0:09:40.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Number 7 helicopter, roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.43,0:09:46.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is helicopter number 7! \NKid isn't hanging from anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.89,0:09:48.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.36,0:09:50.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If he's not hanging from above...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.01,0:09:55.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Nakamori, there's nothing \Nsticking out of this building either!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.92,0:10:00.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I figured, they would suspect that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.32,0:10:05.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But my magic isn't simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.91,0:10:09.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:12.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, on the eve of the main event,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.78,0:10:18.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,feast your eyes on the \Nmiracle I have wrought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.53,0:10:26.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Senior Adviser, shouldn't \Nwe activate that trap now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.56,0:10:28.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:40.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jii-chan's intel was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.83,0:10:42.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's enough for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.83,0:10:49.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's enough of a preview.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.49,0:10:53.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet back here again \Ntomorrow night at 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.91,0:11:00.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-He disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:01.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In mid-air!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.19,0:11:16.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jii-chan, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:18.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The crowd's three times \Nas large tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.49,0:11:20.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.18,0:11:35.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! You're the owner of Blue Wonder \Nand senior adviser of the Suzuki conglomerate,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.34,0:11:37.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Jirokichi-san, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.06,0:11:38.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.08,0:11:39.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.97,0:11:42.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are your Kid countermeasures foolproof?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:46.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night he put on a cut-rate magic show,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.73,0:11:49.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I've got something \Nto show everyone tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.27,0:11:55.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.97,0:11:57.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.52,0:12:12.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,5! 4!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.98,0:12:15.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,3! 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.21,0:12:16.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,1!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:24.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How?! Where did he come from?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.30,0:12:37.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What happened, number 7 chopper? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.29,0:12:38.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:41.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The feed from chopper \Nnumber 7 suddenly cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.03,0:12:44.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is helicopter number 7. I'm not \Nexperiencing any difficulties here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.49,0:12:49.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the rain temporarily \Nscrambled the feed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.49,0:12:53.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. My wager is that Kid \Nhad an assistant cut the power
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:55.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,as part of his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.46,0:12:57.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid has assistants?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:12:59.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.24,0:13:02.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An old man, a young woman... \NThere are various reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.58,0:13:04.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But he definitely has at least one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.47,0:13:09.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get Blue Wonder inside the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.88,0:13:11.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a contest of wits!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.04,0:13:13.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.80,0:13:20.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's in the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.30,0:13:22.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! And now I'll take the initiative.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.61,0:13:25.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Extinguish all the lights \Nin the building immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.38,0:13:27.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn them off?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.48,0:13:31.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible he's intercepting the \Nvideo footage inside the building, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.66,0:13:35.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why put the jewel in the museum?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.29,0:13:39.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The main thing is to not let him steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.80,0:13:47.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.52,0:13:49.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.45,0:13:53.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No problems, Inspector Nakamori. We're \Ndefinitely outthinking Kid with this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.81,0:13:55.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.87,0:13:59.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He may be listening in, \Nso let's cut the chatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.95,0:14:02.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.60,0:14:03.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is going smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.81,0:14:09.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Another dud...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.91,0:14:14.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, at least I got back\N at old man Jirokichi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.19,0:14:17.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,by showing everyone a miracle,\N so not a bad night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.24,0:14:28.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.08,0:14:32.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Kid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.72,0:14:35.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.26,0:14:39.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm laughing because I kept Kid \Nfrom stealing the jewel, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.59,0:14:40.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dumbass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.69,0:14:45.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw right through you the moment you \Narrived at the museum on this bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.15,0:14:49.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, like now, you're \Nnot wearing your goggles.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.60,0:14:54.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear it's really painful for people who \Nwear contacts not to wear goggles when riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.37,0:14:56.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This kid doesn't miss a trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.31,0:15:01.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And an old man riding around in a \Nshowy bike without bodyguards...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.74,0:15:05.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you had any number of chances \Nto put him to sleep and take his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.42,0:15:09.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I "silenced" the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.57,0:15:13.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since he's the type who wants to stand out \Nso much that he interferes with the magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.29,0:15:17.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't be Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.44,0:15:22.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, when Kid appeared \Nearlier, I was right next to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.62,0:15:26.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the moment he performed \Nthat airwalking miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.15,0:15:29.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was no miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.20,0:15:32.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a simple trick that only \Nrequired an assistant and preparation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.86,0:15:35.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It must not have been that hard\N for your assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.90,0:15:40.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,to temporarily slip into the crowd\N of hired helicopter pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.12,0:15:44.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Jii-chan has all kinds of licenses, \Nso it was a cinch for him to be hired.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.96,0:15:50.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,First, you and your assistant flew \Nthe chopper over those two buildings,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.65,0:15:54.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,then attached a wire to one of the roofs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.36,0:16:00.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Toss away the camouflaging \Nblack cape into the stage smoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:02.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and Kid the Phantom Thief appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.15,0:16:09.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, your assistant in the helicopter \Nhovered directly overhead,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:12.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so Kid was "wired" from above and the side,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.93,0:16:15.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,seemingly floating in mid-air.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.78,0:16:18.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you just had to pretend to walk
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.45,0:16:20.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,to match the chopper's slow advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:26.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A music player you had in your pocket \Nplayed the sound of footsteps,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.84,0:16:31.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and your exceptional body performance \Nensured no one would notice you were hanging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.84,0:16:33.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:38.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...for the finishing touch, your assistant \Npulled you up into the chopper,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.73,0:16:41.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,making it look like you \Nvanished into thin air.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.37,0:16:44.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.36,0:16:51.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although {\i1}tonight's{\i0} Kid was just a marionette \Nto draw the police's attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.01,0:16:53.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was obvious to me that \Nit was just hanging there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.93,0:16:57.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But you climbed that building, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.08,0:17:02.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If there was anything hanging from a helicopter,\N you would've seen it, even a thin wire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.33,0:17:04.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Preconceptions and wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.53,0:17:06.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pathetic on my part.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.78,0:17:12.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When the helicopter was over you,\N I didn't think you were hanging from it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.28,0:17:14.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was startled there were \Nno wires on the roof,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.86,0:17:17.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and the wind from the chopper \Nalso made it difficult to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:20.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and so I didn't spot your wires.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.68,0:17:25.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But your hooks left scratches on the roofs \Nof both buildings where they were attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.24,0:17:28.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Preconceptions...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.78,0:17:30.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In magic, we call that the "reappearance."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.49,0:17:36.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you show that there's nothing there once, \Nit's hard for people to get suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.43,0:17:42.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,After they've checked something once,\N they don't feel the need to check again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.87,0:17:48.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure you watched the footage \Nof Kid last night over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.08,0:17:53.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The footage shows a bird's-eye \Nview of Kid, wires and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.90,0:17:57.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but it was shot by your confederate \Nin helicopter number 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:18:02.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd used faked footage based \Non the museum's special exhibition,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.24,0:18:04.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,there's no way the wires would be showing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.77,0:18:09.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But when it started to rain, your assistant \Nnixed the idea of sending out the fake footage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.05,0:18:15.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it didn't show people at the \Nexhibition opening their umbrellas, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.50,0:18:21.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet last night's demonstration, where you \Nseemed to appear from the air, was to loosen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.82,0:18:26.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,ground security so you could come in \Ndisguised as Suzuki Jirokichi without a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.98,0:18:29.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But you were careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:34.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were shown on TV on the bike \Nbut without the goggles on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.90,0:18:38.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I didn't {\i1}forget {\i0}\Nto put the goggles on...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.72,0:18:40.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't put them on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.68,0:18:43.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because that would ruin \Nmy disguise! You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:48.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure about this? Your \Nassistant in chopper number 7...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.49,0:18:51.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He may be surrounded by police \Nhelicopters right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.94,0:18:56.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No worries there. I'm sure \Nthe cops are in panic mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.68,0:19:00.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And confused by all the stickers \Nwe put on number 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.53,0:19:01.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All the stickers?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.66,0:19:03.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.56,0:19:09.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You lightly glued on stickers over the \Noriginal number so they'd peel off in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.83,0:19:11.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.22,0:19:15.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That way, he could slip in with the \Nother pilots without them noticing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.66,0:19:20.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And nobody could chase after his chopper, \Nbecause "number 7" was gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.45,0:19:23.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My friend took advantage \Nof the chaos and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.85,0:19:28.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's your Blue Wonder! \NA miraculous aerial escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.41,0:19:29.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aerial?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.96,0:19:33.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The "blue" in  Blue Wonder refers to the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.02,0:19:34.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Same difference, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.80,0:19:37.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The blue of the sky is reflected \Nin the blue of the sea, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.73,0:19:40.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like detective and phantom thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.67,0:19:42.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They appear to be as different \Nas heaven and earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.92,0:19:46.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but look closely, and you'll see \Nthey're both insolent fellows who use
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.36,0:19:50.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the key of curiosity to pry open something \Nthat someone else wants to keep shut.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.71,0:19:54.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dumbass. The blue of the sky and sea
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.67,0:19:56.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,are from the color's \Ndiffusion and reflection.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.80,0:19:59.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because they're completely \Ndifferent substances.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.76,0:20:01.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not the same thing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.66,0:20:04.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see the proof in a puddle,\N which isn't blue, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.88,0:20:07.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You have no dreams, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.31,0:20:10.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I talked about dreams all the time, \NI wouldn't be able to see through to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.94,0:20:15.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That aside, do you really think you'll \Ncapture me with that tranquilizer gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.00,0:20:18.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If I get knocked out at this speed, \Nwe'll get into a major wreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.40,0:20:19.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.70,0:20:22.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't shoot you until the bike stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.27,0:20:26.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already contacted Inspector Nakamori, \Nso he'll be the one to arrest you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.34,0:20:28.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'm gonna stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.89,0:20:32.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is something old man \NJirokichi is proud about, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.33,0:20:36.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The bike has a trick you can do \Nto get rid of excess weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.19,0:20:45.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See you around, great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.92,0:20:49.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I wasn't really after the jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.16,0:20:52.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This time was just about \Ntaking up the gauntlet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.60,0:20:54.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.23,0:20:59.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't shoot you until the bike stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.58,0:21:03.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That little turd hit the gas tank!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.05,0:21:22.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For them, don't be bound by theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.08,0:21:26.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but intoxicate them with a display \Nof brilliant magic that verges
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.02,0:21:27.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,on the impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.80,0:21:34.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can do that, your troublesome \Nheckler will turn into an ardent fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.68,0:21:39.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how a true magician ought to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.96,0:21:45.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of magic should I use \Nto boggle his mind next time?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.38,0:21:52.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight's performance was \Na miraculous mid-air walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.67,0:21:57.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure even the pint-sized \Ndetective was impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.38,0:22:01.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see you next illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.35,0:23:32.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! That brat's gonna get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.91,0:23:35.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was almost burnt toast back there!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.20,0:23:37.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But my next prey is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.37,0:23:41.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's after the world's biggest emerald, \Nwhich is being used as a prop in a play!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.31,0:23:43.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who gave you permission to do the preview?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.09,0:23:43.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.98,0:23:45.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes a difference!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.23,0:23:48.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}: \NGreen Dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.23,0:23:48.73,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Green Dream
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.73,0:23:51.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Step right this way! Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.61,0:23:53.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.20,0:23:55.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right! It's me! Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.16,0:23:56.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahem...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.25,0:23:58.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the illusion!
